{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_017qqrt6z9Kz55gDQpmggdy9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the `official_image` build strategy:\n1. It uses `official_image_registry` (e.g., `docker.io/library/wordpress`) as the source\n2. It inspects the image using the `source_version` or `build_version` tag candidates\n3. If found, it returns that as the built image\n4. Then `copy_image_to_lazycat` copies it to `registry.lazycat.cloud`\n\nFor the manifest, the build system:\n1. Copies the official WordPress image to `registry.lazycat.cloud`  \n2. The target service is `wordpress` (from `image_targets`)\n\n\n3. The manifest references this with a service-name-as-tag pattern like `:wordpress`, but the actual copied image gets stored with a hash in `.lazycat-images.json` and gets resolved at build time.\n\nSo the placeholder in the manifest will be replaced during the build phase with the real accelerated image reference. The real issue is that the queue state is stuck as `build_failed` when it should be `waiting_for_human` since there's no license, and `registry/repos/index.json` is empty. I need to update the queue entry to reflect the correct state and add a human request for the license.\n\nWriting the Python script...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":825,"cache_read_input_tokens":62918,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":825},"output_tokens":12,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8db3a375-e8d4-4eb3-8dc1-97d932784064","uuid":"3b30bf70-17d3-4753-b01a-bae0d62eb1a9"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_017qqrt6z9Kz55gDQpmggdy9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have full understanding. Here's my assessment:\n\n**Root cause of `build_failed`**: The queue is in `build_failed` state but should be `waiting_for_human` (no license). Also `registry/repos/index.json` is empty — pressyard is not registered there, which would cause \"Config not found\" if a build ran.\n\n**Existing scaffold quality**: Mostly correct — `official_image` strategy, WordPress+MariaDB services, correct image placeholder format for the build system. Minor completeness issues only.\n\nLet me make the needed changes:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":825,"cache_read_input_tokens":62918,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":825},"output_tokens":12,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8db3a375-e8d4-4eb3-8dc1-97d932784064","uuid":"490736c3-0d9a-488b-9e2a-4522696cbb7d"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_017qqrt6z9Kz55gDQpmggdy9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01BchY3Csg9eUebV6nnVheGK","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"python3 - <<'EOF'\nimport json\nfrom datetime import datetime\n\nqueue_path = \"/__w/lzcat-apps/lzcat-apps/registry/auto-migration/queue.json\"\n\nwith open(queue_path) as f:\n    queue = json.load(f)\n\nitems = queue.get(\"items\", [])\nfor item in items:\n    if isinstance(item, dict) and item.get(\"slug\") == \"pressyard\":\n        item[\"state\"] = \"waiting_for_human\"\n        item[\"human_request\"] = {\n            \"kind\": \"license\",\n            \"question\": (\n                \"The upstream repo CodeMasters999/PressYard has NO LICENSE file. \"\n                \"Per migration policy, this requires explicit human approval before proceeding. \"\n                \"Additionally: (1) The repo root contains an unrelated Roblox Lua script alongside \"\n                \"a pinkweed/ directory holding the actual ZIP archive, raising questions about \"\n                \"repo integrity. (2) PressYard is a multi-site WordPress management tool using \"\n                \"Traefik project-based hostname routing — the current scaffold deploys a single \"\n                \"WordPress+MariaDB instance instead, which is a simpler but reduced interpretation. \"\n                \"Please decide: approve migration with UNLICENSED status and confirm single-WP scope, \"\n                \"or reject this migration.\"\n            )\n        }\n        item[\"updated_at\"] = datetime.utcnow().strftime(\"%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ\")\n        item.pop(\"last_error\", None)\n        print(\"Updated pressyard item to waiting_for_human\")\n        break\nelse:\n    print(\"ERROR: pressyard item not found in queue\")\n\nwith open(queue_path, \"w\") as f:\n    json.dump(queue, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False)\n    f.write(\"\\n\")\n\nprint(\"Queue saved.\")\nEOF","description":"Update pressyard queue item to waiting_for_human with license human_request"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":825,"cache_read_input_tokens":62918,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":825},"output_tokens":12,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8db3a375-e8d4-4eb3-8dc1-97d932784064","uuid":"4d1b1289-1c80-40b1-b45a-0b03a47c13c5"}
